article.headline: Bowling Green 86, Morehead St. 70
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Ryne Hamblet and Nate Miller each scored 16 and three other Falcons reached double figures as Bowling Green beat Morehead State 86-70 Saturday. Bowling Green (3-1) were ahead throughout and used 66.7 percent shooting to keep Morehead State (1-2) from threatening. The Falcons built a 19-point lead with 3:38 left in the first half -- their largest lead -- and the Eagles only got as close as eight the rest of the game. The Eagles shot just 39.2 percent, but Leon Buchanan scored 35 points and was 15 of 15 from the free throw line. John Lamb added 11 points. Bowling Green's Marc Larson scored 14 points, Darryl Clements had 11 and Chris Knight 10.
